1. Explain what the terminal is in your own words.
It is a command line that lets you interact with your computer using text commands. You can tell your computer what to do using words instead of clicking buttons. 

2. What is the major difference between Git and GitHub?
GitHub is the platform that stores the Git repositories and makes it easy to collaborate. Git tracks changes to code while it's being developed.


3. What are the steps to fork a GitHub repository?
Find your repository in your GitHub account. 
Copy the SSH
Use the command Git clone <SSH>
cd into your repository
git commit ~m "any changes you did to your code"
git push

These are the steps you need to take in the terminal to fork a GitHub repository.
